    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-24T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-24T01:00:00-05:00" n="595"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8–2444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-24T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 24, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1451. In telegram 19th Tihwa reports Lo Chia-lun convinced August 12 plot to kill
                    Sheng Shih-tsai actually existed. Soviets had paid large bribes to Sheng’s
                    principal subordinates for participation and Sheng’s July-August reports of
                    almost open Soviet aid to Kazaks fully reliable. (Retel 1419, August 16th and
                    1434, August 19th.) Consul considers these reports possibly manufactured or
                    exaggerated by Sheng.</p>
                <p>In telegram 20th Tihwa reports Lo and Chu Shao-liang left Tihwa for Chungking to
                    see Generalissimo and that Lo said Sheng’s relationship with Chungking being
                    readjusted and Lo almost certain solution will bring much increased Chungking
                    influence Tihwa. Consul skeptical such solution will eventuate, pointing out
                    Kuomintang Director and Commissioner Reconstruction still detained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
